      <div type="commentary" xml:lang="en">
	<p>This edition is based on <ref target="bibl:Sarma1993">Sarma and Varaprasada Rao 1993</ref>. They have, however, incorrectly classified this inscription as an “Epigraph of a Sātavāhana Ruler.” The translation is mine (AO).</p>
      </div>
      <div type="edition" xml:lang="mi-Latn">

	<p>
	  <lb n="1"/>
	  <app><lem source="#ARIE1968">ṇ<unclear>hā</unclear></lem><rdg
	            source="#Sarma1993">nhā</rdg></app>sa 
	  bhāradāyasa <app><lem wit="#Sarma1993">kuṭu</lem><rdg
	    source="#ARIE1968">kūtu</rdg></app>bi<app><lem 
	    source="#Sarma1993">na mahā</lem><rdg 
	    source="#ARIE1968">nam aha</rdg></app>tarakasa 
	  mahāsāthavāhanasa <persName
	    key="pers:Sa-Agniśarman"><app><lem resp="#AO">agnisa</lem><rdg
	    source="#Sarma1993">agnisa</rdg><rdg
	    source="#ARIE1968">agiṣa</rdg></app>ma<supplied 
	    reason="lost">sa</supplied></persName>
	</p>
      </div>
      <div type="translation">
	<p>
	  Of the Mahattaraka and caravan-merchant 
	  <persName key="pers:Sa-Agniśarman">Agniśarman</persName>,
	  who belongs to the Bharadvāja clan...
	</p>
      </div>
